TUS REPORT ON THE MAP CATALOGING PROJECT AT THE ILLINOIS STATE LIBRARY.     ILLINOIS STATE LIBRARY BEGAN ITS MAP CATALOGUING PROJECT ON 1 AUG 80. ALLFORMERLY UNCATALOGUED SHEET MAPS ARE BEING CATALOGUED IN MARC MAP FORMAT ANDTHOSE ALREADY CATALOGUED BY VARIOUS METHODS ARE BEING RECATALOGUED, USINGOCLC. BECAUSE THE STATE LIBRARY IS A REGIONAL GOVERNMENT PRINTING OFFICEDEPOSITORY, THE FEDERAL MAPS ARE BEING CLASSIFIED ACCORDING TO THE SUDOC(SUPERINTENDENT OF DOCUMENTS) SYSTEM. ALL OTHER MAPS ARE BEING CLASSIFIED BYTHE LIBRARY OF CONGRESS G SYSTEM. DESCRIBES PROGRESS ON THE PROJECT ANDDISCUSSES PROBLEMS ENCOUNTERED AND THEIR SOLUTION